This is a modified version of one the [file-save hooks](https://jupyter-notebook.readthedocs.io/en/latest/extending/savehooks.html) to handle adding meta-data to the notebook as well as to each of the cells ... the idea being that it ignores adding the meta-data if it pre-exists.  While adding the notebook meta-data is straight-forward (first part of script below), programmatically adding the cell meta-data is failing.  It seems the cell meta-data isn't getting persisted back to the `model`, although I can see correctly generated cell UUIDs, if I open the notebook in the jupyterlab text editor.  The problem arises when it comes to adding new cells and re-saving, it ends up generating new IDs for each cell (when it should have disregarded those with this info already in place, only generated IDs for new cells).

```
def add_metadata_pre_save(model, **kwargs):
    """adds basic notebook meta-data"""
    # only run on notebooks
    if model['type'] != 'notebook':
        return
    # only run on nbformat v4
    if model['content']['nbformat'] != 4:
        return
    # determine if notebook metadata pre-exists
    # if it does not, then let's add some.
    if 'nb_test' not in  model['content']['metadata']:
        nb_metadata = {'id': str(uuid.uuid4()), 'ProjectId': '12345'}
